<header class="hero springboard-hero" style="background:linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(42,30,90,.95),rgba(42,30,90,.58)),url('https://launchpadinw.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/IMG_4451-scaled.jpeg');background-size:cover;background-position:center">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow">Springboard</div>
    <h1>We help startups validate their idea and get traction.</h1>
    <p>Springboard is a 90-day, hands-on sprint for Inland Northwest founders who need structure, customer discovery, business model clarity, and a practical path toward momentum.</p>
    <div class="buttonrow">
      <a class="btn" href="#apply">Apply to Springboard</a>
      <a class="btn alt" href="#process">See the Process</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<main>
  <section class="section white">
    <div class="container split visual-split">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow purple-eyebrow">What it is</div>
        <h2>A founder sprint built around validation.</h2>
        <p class="lead">Springboard helps early-stage tech and life science companies in the Inland Northwest test the business, learn from customers, and prepare for the next right step.</p>
        <p>The goal is not to make founders look busy. The goal is to help companies gain traction and become more investable through a clear process, expert feedback, and community support.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="panel emphasis-panel">
        <h3>Springboard is for founders who need:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Problem and customer validation</li>
          <li>Lean canvas and business model development</li>
          <li>Go-to-market thinking and early traction</li>
          <li>Pitch, advisor, and investor readiness</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="process" class="section alt process-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow purple-eyebrow">Process</div>
      <h2>From idea to traction.</h2>
      <p class="lead">The process moves founders through foundation building, customer discovery, and business development — using InnovateINW colors and a clearer sequence.</p>
      <div class="process-timeline">
        <div class="phase phase-gold">
          <div class="phase-label">Phase 1</div>
          <h3>Foundation Building</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Initial meeting and approval</li>
            <li>Lean canvas development</li>
            <li>Customer discovery</li>
            <li>Problem / solution fit</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="phase phase-teal">
          <div class="phase-label">Phase 2</div>
          <h3>Build, Measure, Learn</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Prototype or MVP learning</li>
            <li>Market and customer testing</li>
            <li>Go-to-market strategy</li>
            <li>Traction milestones</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="phase phase-purple">
          <div class="phase-label">Phase 3</div>
          <h3>Business Development</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>Financial, legal, and operations review</li>
            <li>Pitch deck development</li>
            <li>Advisor pitch sessions</li>
            <li>Program graduation</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section white learning-loop-section">
    <div class="container split visual-split">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow purple-eyebrow">Learning Loop</div>
        <h2>Build. Measure. Learn.</h2>
        <p class="lead">Springboard keeps founders focused on the loop that matters: build the smallest useful experiment, measure what customers actually do, and learn what to change next.</p>
        <p>That rhythm keeps the work practical. Founders leave with evidence, not just opinions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bml-cycle" aria-label="Build Measure Learn cycle">
        <div class="bml-node build"><strong>Build</strong><span>MVP / experiment</span></div>
        <div class="bml-arrow arrow-one">→</div>
        <div class="bml-node measure"><strong>Measure</strong><span>Customer evidence</span></div>
        <div class="bml-arrow arrow-two">→</div>
        <div class="bml-node learn"><strong>Learn</strong><span>Next decision</span></div>
        <div class="bml-arrow arrow-three">↺</div>
        <div class="bml-center">Validated<br>Learning</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt testimonial-section">
    <div class="container testimonial-card">
      <div class="testimonial-photo" style="background-image:url('https://launchpadinw.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Jennifer-Wilde-Springboard-Client.png')"></div>
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow purple-eyebrow">Founder Testimonial</div>
        <h2>“Springboard has been an invaluable partner in turning my vision into reality.”</h2>
        <p class="testimonial-quote">“As a nurse with no prior business experience, I was overwhelmed by the complexities of launching a startup. Springboard guided me every step of the way—from refining my idea with the lean canvas method to developing a fully functional app that is already making a difference in ER nurse training. Their support in securing funding and connecting me with the right advisors has been instrumental in the early success of WildeCare Education. I couldn’t have done it without them.”</p>
        <p class="testimonial-name">Jennifer Wilde — Springboard Client</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section white photo-proof-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow purple-eyebrow">People, not just programs</div>
      <h2>More of the community on the page.</h2>
      <p class="lead">The site should feel like the Inland Northwest innovation community — founders in rooms, workshops in motion, and real people helping each other build.</p>
      <div class="photo-gallery compact-gallery">
        <div class="photo-card" style="background-image:url(https://launchpadinw.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/HA2_1688.jpeg)"><span>Regional innovation event</span></div>
        <div class="photo-card" style="background-image:url(https://launchpadinw.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/IMG_4463-scaled.jpeg)"><span>Founder workshop</span></div>
        <div class="photo-card" style="background-image:url(https://launchpadinw.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_2503-scaled.jpeg)"><span>Community detail</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="apply" class="section alt apply-section">
    <div class="container split visual-split">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow purple-eyebrow">Apply</div>
        <h2>Tell us how to route you.</h2>
        <p class="lead">Use the Springboard application to share where you are, what you are building, and how InnovateINW can help route you to the right next step.</p>
        <p>This embedded Copper form captures the Springboard application directly for follow-up.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="formbox copper-box">
        <iframe src="https://forms.copper.com/j/aN6NdSNddtWbc1t8mGswS2?type=embed" id="aN6NdSNddtWbc1t8mGswS2" title="Embedded Copper Forms" width="500" height="700" frameborder="0"></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

